SIMPLE: unveil
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unveil
<hw>Un*veil"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>veil</ets>.]</ety> <def>To remove a veil from; to
divest of a veil; to uncover; to disclose to view; to reveal; <as>as,
she <ex>unveiled</ex> her face</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unveil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unveil
<hw>Un*veil"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To remove a veil; to reveal
one's self.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unveiler</ent>⟦br⟧
